olive oil
1 carrot
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
2 clove garlic
20 g butter
¾ cup water
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet couscous
1 packet Slivered Almonds
½ tsp salt
1 tsp plain flour
1 egg
1 packet panko breadcrumbs
1 packet chicken breast
½ lemon
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 packet Garlic Dip

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Slice carrot into half-moons.
• Place carrot and peeled & chopped pumpkin on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and pepper and toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, finely chop garlic.
• In a medium saucepan, melt the butter over a medium-high heat. Cook garlic until fragrant, 1 minute. Add the water and chicken-style stock powder and bring to the boil.
• Add couscous and stir to combine. Cover with a lid and remove from the heat. Set aside until the water has absorbed, 5 minutes. Fluff up with a fork.

• Heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat. Toast slivered almonds, tossing, until golden, 3-4 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.
• In a shallow bowl, combine the salt, plain flour and Aussie spice blend, then season with pepper. In a second shallow bowl, whisk the egg. In a third shallow bowl, add panko breadcrumbs.
• Cut chicken breast into 2cm-thick strips. Coat chicken in flour mixture, followed by egg, and finally the panko breadcrumbs.
• Return frying pan to a medium-high heat with enough olive oil to coat base. When oil is hot, cook chicken until golden, 3-4 minutes each side. Transfer to a plate lined with paper towel.

TIP: Cook chicken in batches if your pan is getting crowded!

• Meanwhile, cut lemon into wedges. Roughly chop baby spinach leaves.
• Add roasted veggies, baby spinach, a squeeze of lemon juice and a drizzle of olive oil to couscous. Toss to combine and season to taste.
• Divide lemony roast veggie couscous between bowls. Top with crumbed chicken strips.
• Garnish with toasted almonds. Serve with garlic dip and any remaining lemon wedges.